


TASK 3: SECURE CODING REVIEW
Title:Secure Coding Review of a PHP Web Application

Selected Application
Programming Language: PHP
Application: Login and Registration System

Review Methods
Security analysis was conducted using:
* SonarQube
* PHPStan
* Manual code inspection

Identified Vulnerabilities
SQL Injection
Vulnerable code: 
php
$query="SELECT * FROM users WHERE username='$username'";

Risk:
* Database compromise
* Unauthorized access

Secure code:
php
$stmt=$conn->prepare("SELECT * FROM users WHERE username=?");
Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
Vulnerable:
php
echo $_GET['name'];
Secure:
php
echo htmlspecialchars($_GET['name']);

Weak Password Storage
Vulnerable:
php
$password=$_POST['password'];
Secure:
php
password_hash($password,PASSWORD_DEFAULT);
 Poor Session Management
Secure implementation:
php
session_regenerate_id(true);






 Secure Coding Best Practices
* Validate all inputs
* Use prepared statements
* Hash passwords
* Use HTTPS
* Apply least privilege
* Update libraries regularly
* Avoid exposing error details

FINDINGS SUMMARY

| Vulnerability    | Risk Level | Recommendation      |
| ---------------- | ---------: | ------------------- |
| SQL Injection    |       High | Prepared statements |
| XSS              |       High | Output encoding     |
| Weak passwords   |       High | Password hashing    |
| Session issues   |     Medium | Regenerate IDs      |
| Input validation |     Medium | Sanitize inputs     |

 CONCLUSION
The review identified several vulnerabilities that could lead to security breaches. Following secure coding practices significantly reduces attack risks and strengthens application security.
